@wordwrap
@tab 8

@node sect0 "Name"
samlabel - label a MasterDOS diskette 
@endnode

@node sect1 "Synopsis"
@{b}samlabel@{ub} [ @{b}-diskfile @{ub}@{i}file@{ui} ] [ @{b}-@{ub}@{i}n@{ui} ] [ @{b}label@{ub} ] 
@endnode

@node sect2 "Description"
@{i}Samlabel@{ui} gives a new label to a MasterDOS diskette.  It may be also used to turn a SAMDOS diskette into a MasterDOS diskette.  If used on a blank diskette it may also be used to set the number of directory tracks used. @{i}Samlabel@{ui} may be used to label a disk image rather than a real floppy by setting the environment variable SAMDISKFILE to the name of the image file or by supplying the @{b}-diskfile @{ub}@{i}file@{ui} flag.  If used this flag must be written first on the command line. It may be abbreviated to @{b}-disk @{ub}@{i}file.@{ui} 

If the @{b}-@{ub}@{i}n@{ui} flag is given, then @{i}n@{ui} gives the number of directory tracks to reserve on the disk.  This number must be between 4 and 39 inclusive.  The disk must be completely blank for this to work. 

If the label name is given, then the disk will be given that name.  If the name is omitted then the name will not change, unless the disk was previously in SAMDOS format: in this case the disk will be named MASTERDOS. 


@endnode

@node sect3 "See Also"
samtools(1) 
@endnode
